This topic outlines the steps for installing and configuring the <%= vars.product_full %>.

## <a id='install'></a> Install and Set Up <%= vars.product_short %> for Apps

1. [Install <%= vars.product_short %>](./installation.html) using <%= vars.ops_manager %>.

1. [Create a Service Plan](./manage-service-plans.html#create-svc-plan).
<%= vars.product_short %> is a multi-tenant service and a service plan
corresponds to a tenant.
This enables an enterprise to separate users or environments using plans.
Each service plan is accessible at a tenant-specific URL in the format
`https://AUTH-DOMAIN.login.SYSTEM-DOMAIN`.

1. [Create a Service Instance](./manage-service-instances.html#create-svc-instance).
<%= vars.product_short %> plans can provide single sign-on capabilities for
applications in various spaces.
A service instance lets you bind an application to a service plan.

1. [Configure an Identity Provider](./configure-internal-us.html).
In addition to the [Internal User Store](./configure-internal-us.html#config-int-store),
you can configure [External Identity Providers](./configure-external-id.html#config-ext-prov)
to provide single sign-on to applications.

1. [Configure Your Applications](./config-apps.html).
<%= vars.product_short %> supports <%= vars.app_runtime_full %> apps as well
as externally hosted apps.
Your applications must be able to request an OAuth or OpenID Connect token.

1. [Create Resources for Your Applications](./manage-resources.html#create-resources).
If your registered applications need to make external API calls, you can assign
the API endpoints as resources permitted for the application.
This adds the endpoints to an allowlist for use by the application or client.

## <a id='roles'></a> <%= vars.product_short %> User Roles

User roles determine the parts of a <%= vars.product_short %> configuration that a user can view or manage.
<%= vars.product_short %> uses the following user roles:

+ **<%= vars.ops_manager %> Administrators,** who can manage service plans, service instances,
identity providers (IdPs), apps, and resources. This is a <%= vars.ops_manager %> user role.
+ **Plan Administrators,** who can manage service instances, IdPs, apps, and resources. This is
a user role that is specific to <%= vars.product_short %>.
+ **Space Developers,** who can manage service instances, apps, and resources.
This is an <%= vars.ops_manager %> user role.
+ **Space Auditors,** who can view service instances, apps, and resources.
They cannot edit any configurations.
This is an <%= vars.ops_manager %> user role.

